SIMPLE: escaloped
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Escaloped
<hw>Es*cal"oped</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Cut or
marked in the form of an escalop; scalloped.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Her.)</fld> <def>Covered with a pattern resembling
a series of escalop shells, each of which issues from between two
others. Its appearance is that of a surface covered with
scales.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Escaloped oysters</b></col> <fld>(Cookery)</fld>. <cd>See
under <er>Scalloped</er>.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Escambio</ent>⟦br⟧
